The paper focuses on the generation and editing of machine-generated stories, which falls under the domain of natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The study also involves human-computer interaction, which suggests cs.HC as a likely sub-category. The analysis of the edits made by users involves statistical analysis, indicating cs.LG as another possible sub-category. Finally, the study involves text editing and optimization, which suggests cs.IR as a possible sub-category.
